CLOSED 2026-06-10: this ticket was misplaced.

DBD::Sybase is not a dbio-mssql concern. The cpanfile declaration belongs
in dbio-sybase (karr #7 on dbio-sybase board). Once that lands, running
  cpanm --installdeps .
from dbio-mssql will pull DBD::Sybase in transitively via
  dbio-mssql -> DBIO::Sybase -> DBD::Sybase

At that point t/10 + t/20 can be re-enabled by un-skipping their
plan skip_all blocks. (Or, if those tests turn out to be better-homed
in dbio-sybase, delete them from dbio-mssql — separate decision.)

Install path documented in dbio-sybase #7:
  apt install freetds-dev
  SYBASE=/usr cpanm DBD::Sybase

